<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.Q.13.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Article 25</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p>Czechoslovakia’s interests are not covered either by the proposal of the
                            Soviet Union or by that of U.S.A., the U.K. and France. The Czechoslovak
                            delegation will present its point of view during the discussion on art.
                            25.</p>
                    </div>
